[SN]TITLE[SN]
Peter Baker: Tottenham double-winning right-back dies

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Former Tottenham Hotspur right-back Peter Baker, who was a part of the club's 1961 double-winning team, has died following illness aged 84.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Baker joined Spurs in June 1949 and made 342 appearances.
He won the league title, two FA Cups and the 1963 European Cup Winners' Cup under Bill Nicholson.
A club statement said: "It is with great sadness that we announce the death of our former double-winning right-back Peter Baker."
Baker left White Hart Lane in the summer of 1965 and emigrated to South Africa, where he played for Durban United.
